4  Covariance Data                                                4034 1451
==================                                                4034 1451
                                                                  4034 1451
   The covariance data was taken from the 93Zr evalaution in the  4034 1451
COMMARA-2.0 library [6].                                          4034 1451
  In thermal and resolved resonance region we made use of the     4034 1451
covariance formalism based on the kernel approximation along      4034 1451
with data in the Atlas of Neutron Resonances.                     4034 1451
  In fast neutron region up to 20 MeV covariance estimates were   4034 1451
calculated using the nuclear reaction code EMPIRE and the         4034 1451
Bayesian code KALMAN. The KALMAN code along with selected         4034 1451
experimental data was used to determine the correlation matrix    4034 1451
of the model parameters. Furthermore, additional parameters       4034 1451
scaling total and absorption cross sections were included to      4034 1451
prevent the unrealistic drop in the cross-section uncertainties   4034 1451
and, in some instance. In the case of 93-Zr, for which central    4034 1451
value of the cross sections calculated by EMPIRE considerably     4034 1451
differed from those in ENDF/B-VII.0 evaluations, we applied       4034 1451
dispersion analysis. For all zirconium isotopes the total         4034 1451
cross-section uncertainties were computed as the sum of elastic,  4034 1451
inelastic, (n2n), and capture.                                    4034 1451
